storyInfo: Lungmen has welcomed a great number of outsiders. A wolf pack, a pack leader, a lone wolf... Slowly and quietly, they all find themselves shaped by the concrete jungle... until it is time for them to heed the call of the wild.

attributes.content: 9:35. Five minutes late.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: We'd better find another place. For safety.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I don't want to spend a second more than I have to, but you know what want even less? To miss our contact.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: He's supposed to come straight to us first thing after getting into Lungmen, but there ain't a single soul coming out of city gate. He's probably stuck somewhere inside. So we wait.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Too many eyes here at the city gateway. You sure you wanna stick around?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What else are we gonna do? We gotta do what the psycho bitch wants!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You remember the first thing she said after she caught us?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: 'Changed my mind. Let's hope you're more useful to me alive than dead.'
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Not that thing! The next one!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: 'Don't blow this. Mess up a single time, I cut your throats.'
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: So, so instead of risking missin' our guy and losin' the letter, I'd rather be a little more conspicuous.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Youâ€”Whatever.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: There's the crowd.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What does the guy look like again?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Don't hurt yourself trying to remember. It's not going to happen.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What do you mean?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: *sigh*.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: The broad never said anything about what our contact looked like or what he's wearin'. He'll come to us, not the other way around.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: You remember how the meeting goes down, right?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Gambino?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: The contact asks us, 'Would you like some mayonnaise teppanyaki macaroni,' we'll tell him, 'Supersize, for two,' and he'll give us the letter.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I'm impressed.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Just hearing that password makes me wanna puke. Couldn't forget it even if I wanted to.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: It's 9:50. Even the last group into the city is gone by now.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Something must've gone wrong. We should move.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What if he shows and we ain't here?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Like that could happen. We can't just stand around any longer!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Maybe customs busted him?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Even if not, no harm in waitin' for him a little longer. It's his own damned fault he didn't find us. The crazy bitch can't do nothing about that...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What's the difference?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: She's off her goddamned rocker. She ain't gonna think about who's at fault here, it's all about results! If you don't move your furry ass right now, you're signing our death certificates!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Alright, let's say I do it your way. Where do we look for him?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Use your brain.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Only a Siracusan would write the looney broad a letter. Aside from Penguin Logistics, who else in Lungmen's got anythin' to do with Siracusa?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: You tellin' me it's the traitors we brought with us from the old country?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Not only did they betray us, they're nabbing our guy?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Heh, guess you do still got a couple of brain cells to rub together.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Can't say for sure it was them, but they do fit the profile. They're gonna know something, at least.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Andiamo.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Those traitorous cazzi. One day, I swear I'm gonnaâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Hold it!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I've been telling you since the first day we stepped into Lungmen. They got their own rules here.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Don't forget how we lost to the Rat King, and how he let us go without a scratch.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Don't need the reminder, Capone!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I sure hope so.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: So, we're droppin' in on the traitors' hideout. We ain't there to pick a fight or teach 'em a lesson. Just doin' a little information gathering. You hear me?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Slow down. This is the place.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: How do you feel?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Never better.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What's the plan? Grab a couple and start askin' questions?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Probably a better way.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: If they're the mooks who kidnapped our Messenger guy from Siracusa, then it's somethin' their bosses cooked up. And if it wasn't them, then these small timers ain't gonna know anything.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: It's times like these you actually give that brain a little workout, huh?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: So, how are we runnin' this one? Like we did in the old days? You go make some noise while I sneak in?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Not so fast. We gotta case the joint a little longer. Don't take a risk if their guard is low enough.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: We're working for the crazy broad. I need all the help I can get, even if you usually do more harm than good.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Hah, listen to yourself. If it wasn't for me, you woulda screwed up enough for the psycho to run you through.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Haha, twenty-one!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Hell yeah, come to papa!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Hold on, what the hell's that?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: What's what? You better pay upâ€”
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: We got a cheat!
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: (Quietly) The lookouts are playin' cards in broad daylight?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: (Quietly) If I were their boss, I'd shove the whole deck down their throats.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Save it. Who do you even think you are now?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: (Quietly) Besides, it's pretty convenient for us they ain't payin' attention.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: *Sigh*... I lost big this time.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Haven't been paid jack for a while now. Wouldn't've been playin' otherwise.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: What, you think I'm loaded? You were tryin' to steal from me!
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Your turf is close to the markets. At least you can pick up some odd jobs and run errands around there. Me? I gotta stroll around the Infected camp. Place's like a graveyard. No work at all, even if I tried looking for some!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Odd jobs?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Who's there?!
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: What? What was that?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: I heard someone say something just now, and pretty damned close.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: What did they say?
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: I think it was... 'odd jobs?'
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: Hahahaha... You're hearin' things. Or some punk's tryin' to spook you.
attributes.name: Mafioso B

attributes.content: Maybe.
attributes.name: Mafioso A

attributes.content: (Quietly) Are you outta your mind?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: (Quietly) No...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Back when we picked up these kids, when we made them Gambinos, Sicilians...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Did ever think they'd end up... errand boys?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Outta my mind? What was all those years of blood, sweat, and tears for? What are they in this for?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) To live another day, you egomaniac!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: (Quietly) This is all good news, with the shape we're in. And you're complaining?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: (Quietly) Of course I'm complaining! How am I supposedâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Shit! They're packing heat?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: No, that's an Originium explosion. A couple blocks away, from the sound of itâ€”Where are you going?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: You wanna stay here your whole life?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Slow down!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: G-Gambino, you're running tooâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Capone suddenly finds himself speechless, just as Gambino did when he reached the area a dozen or so seconds ago.
A man wearing a black hat and raincoat stands in front of them.
A number of local Lungmenite triads lies on the ground around him. Some of them are unconscious, while others are groaning as they hold their wounds, but they are all alive.
Would you like some mayonnaise teppanyaki macaroni?
attributes.name: Man in Black

attributes.content: Yeah... Supersize, for two.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Buon appetito.
attributes.name: Man in Black

attributes.content: Capone walks a few steps forward and takes a letter from the man in black.
The wax seal on the envelope seems familiar, but he doesn't immediately recognize what it represents.
Buongiorno, which family do youâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Bossâ€”No, Mr... Gambino?
attributes.name: Man in Black

attributes.content: Tommaso?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What are you doing hereâ€”No, who gave you this letter? Where's the guy you got this from?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I-I don't know! The letter's from me!
attributes.name: Tommaso

attributes.content: I know what kind of man you are, Tommaso. You can't fool me.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I know you don't have what it takes to put all these men on the ground by yourself. They'd beat you half-dead. The letter man's gotta be the one who did this.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You'll tell me where he went, if you know what's good for you.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I... I can't.
attributes.name: Tommaso

attributes.content: Looks like you got pretty forgetful since I been gone.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Then I guess I'll gotta squeeze it outta you! You'll beg for death.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Tommaso

attributes.content: I won't tell you, no matter what! Not even if you kill me!
attributes.name: Tommaso

attributes.content: Alright, you asked for itâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Gambino!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Since when did you get all sentimental? If we find the letter man, we might just get a way out of this godforsaken town, back to...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Look at the envelope, the seal. Don't tell me you don't know what that is.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: It's... from her? Why would she... Why's she thinkin' about Lungmen?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Crap, it's the L.G.D.! They're here lookin' into the blast!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Tommaso, come with usâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: He's gone?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Don't worry about him. We're in enough trouble!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Drop your weapons... surrounded...
attributes.name: Indistinct Voice

attributes.content: This way.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: That's a dead end!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Trust me! Hurry!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I-Is this a gang war?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: No, looks more like a one-sided power move... See? They're all alive.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: You're right. They're hurt pretty damned bad, though.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: The perp can't be far! Let's move!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: Which way?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: We have patrols on both ends of the street. If they had even half a brain, they'd have gone down this alley.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: Hah, I know this alley. It's a dead end.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: (Quietly) This is your idea of a way out?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Didn't you hear 'em? They got men posted on both ends of the street. We're trapped!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Alright, come on out. You can't hide!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: Seeing as you didn't kill any of them, we'll go easy on you.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: Stop resisting. Come out already!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: (Quietly) They're gonna find us!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) Shut up. I'm thinking. I'm thinking...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: We know you're hiding behind that wall. Drop your weapons and come on out!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: (Quietly) Got anything yet?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Quietly) I'm thinking. I'mâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I'll say it again. Drop your weapons, and we'll go easyâ€”
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: In your dreams!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Freezeâ€”
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: Stop! Stop right there!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: Now, make a run for it!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What? He's got an accomplice. Is this a diversion? Quick! Call for backupâ€”
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer B

attributes.content: He's got at least one accomplice. They have crossbows. Terrible aim!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer A

attributes.content: Terrible what?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: If this wasn't Lungmen, I woulda blown your brains out!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: *pant*... *pant*...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: They probably won't catch us here.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: All we ever do these days is run, hmph. And all because of a few punks?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: It's just like you to say that, you egomaniac.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: That arrogant air of yours gets more intense the harder we're screwed. It pisses me off more than it did when we were young.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What? Takin' a trip down memory lane?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: A little.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I still remember who gave me this last arrow wound here.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: And if I weren't in the same boat as that cazzo right now, I'd give him one to match, a little closer to his heart. No point in going down memory lane otherwise.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Yeah, you're damned right.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: And I'd love to stick another arrow in that arrogant bastard. The brain this time. I won't miss.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Hah, nice. If you wanna do me in so badly, why don't we get right down to it?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: You think I'm scared of you?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What else could it be? You couldn't take me down, not without gettin' the jump on me.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: (Deep breath)
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Sure, I couldn't take you in a fight.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Oh? Finally admitting it?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Don't forget who we work for... You brought her up earlier, now it's my turn to remind you.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Looks like you're still sane enough to calm down. Thank God.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I'm still worried, though. After all, we didn't get the letter from the real contact. You think that crazy broad might say we messed up?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Hell would I know?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: All I know is the two of us together wouldn't last ten seconds against her.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Ain't like we got a choice, so why worry about it?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: I can smell you two through the door. You've been standing outside for a while. What's up?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: N-Nothing, ma'am. All's well. Everythin's just fine. We got the letter.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Everything's fine?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Yeah, it all went really well. Great, even.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: It all went well, but it took you this long to come back?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Show me the letter.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: D-Done already? Y-You read it that fast?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Got a problem?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: N-No, not at all. No problems with that. Not a single one. No opinions even.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Feels like you still have something to say, though?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: What he's tryin' to say is... Does that letter talk about us at all?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Haha, hahahahaha.... HAHAHAHAHA!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Well?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: The letter says I can deal with you two however I like.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: What's the matter? No reaction to that bit of information?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Is... Is that really it?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Heh, never would've thought. You've got a nose for this sort of thing.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: The letter says that, considering what absolute failures, what miserable embarrassments you two have been, I should dig a hole somewhere out in the barrenlands and leave you six feet deep.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You don't seem very surprised.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: What's to be surprised about? Even I think we're embarrassing.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: So, what'cha gonna do?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Take your own lives in disgrace?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You could try to make a run for it again. I'll give you fifteen whole seconds this time.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Don't joke about that. We know the score.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Heh.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Alright, I have another idea.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You two never actually meant all that much to them in the first place.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You know their rules, right? Stop fooling yourselves. Signora Sicilia isn't going to care about two rabid stray dogs. Hell, she doesn't even care about me.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You two know what that means. It's Siracusa itself that wants you two gone.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: I don't really care much about that, but even I think you two desperate puppies are a pathetic sight.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: So, why don't you duel it out?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: That'll get you back some of that so-called honor, the one who wrote the letter ends up in a better mood, and I'll get me some quiet time.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: How about it? Whaddya think?!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: A blood pact, then...
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: What was that?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: If we go against the letter's instructions, betray our own Family, and even make a pact with you, you'll only be able to protect the one who lives, right?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Pact? Protect? Betrayal?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Do I have to tell you guys how many times you've stabbed each other in the back? Me?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Alright... I accept.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Capone?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Didn't you just tell me there's no point in going down memory lane?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Alright, I'm in. I'll count to three, and that's when we'll go. We'll see who lives.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: And by the way, I didn't strike before I finished talkin'. That's me makin' it up to you for all those times I stabbed you in the back.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Alright, traitor. We'll call it square.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Tre...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Due...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Uno!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Fight!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Hahahaha... Hahahahaha! HAHAHAHA!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: I love that!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: More! Give me more! Free the hate in your hearts! Show me just how far you can go when your lives are on the line!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Gambino, now!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Graaaahhhh!!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Take thisâ€”
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: To the left!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: No way... She didn't even draw her swordâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Amateurs. I know where your attacks are coming from without even really looking.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You make a good couple of brothers. The dumb one is dumb as hell, and the one that looks smart only looks it.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: I bet you two didn't have it that hard back in Siracusa when you were little. Life must've been comfortable?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Gambino, don't give her the room to talkâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: No way! Barehanded?!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Is that so surprising?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: It's like we come from two totally different Siracusas.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Just like this.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: How does it feel to have your own crossbow bolt pressed against your throat?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Can't say I'm feelin' a lot.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Since you didn't like my idea, I'll have to follow the letter and dispose of you two in whatever way pleases me.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You forgot about one thing.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What's that?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: This is Lungmen.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: So?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You can't cut a throat with rubber-tipped bolts!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: I knew you had a knife on you. Didn't expect you to be so quick to draw it.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: But still... too slow!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Gughâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: And sure, these bolts with rubber heads can't kill.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: But it's not so hard to find your aorta.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: *chokes*
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Capone?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Ugh... Guhâ€”
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*!
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Congrats. You saved your life.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: *cough*... So what? You're still gonna...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Save it, Capone.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: We should've died here a long time ago. Let's at least go out like real Sicilians.
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: For a brief moment, Gambino and Capone think they are seeing things.
They see Lappland holding the exquisitely decorated envelope and the neatly unfolded letter above an open flame.
A corner of the letter lights up.
Are you nuts?! You... You burned Signora Sicilia's letter?!
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: Oh? You didn't think I was nuts?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: It's a letter full of pretentious, make-believe honor tripe. Feels much better to just burn it.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: This... crazy bitch...
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What, you're going to stick up for her?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: I wouldn't dare.
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Now that's the truth. You wouldn't dare. Neither of you. Whether it's baring your fangs against her or sticking up for her, you wouldn't dare.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You think she chased you out of your homeland, but you don't dare speak up.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Aren't you angry? Don't you think it's her fault you got exiled from Siracusa?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Are you really so scared of her? Even though she says right in the letter she wants you dead, you still can't stand seeing that very letter burn?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Ugh. Lame.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Get up.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Where are you... taking us?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: Taking you? Why should I have to take you anywhere?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Aren't you going to bury us out in the wastes?
attributes.name: Capone

attributes.content: What you two did was clumsy as hell, but it wasn't like, completely embarrassing.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Also, the letter's gone now, so why should I still listen to her?
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: Alright, get up!
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: You've got work to do. You can't just be lying around on the ground.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: What work?
attributes.name: Gambino

attributes.content: There's more than one lone wolf in this city.
attributes.name: Lappland

attributes.content: What do you think of Lungmen tea?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Seems it's not to your taste. I've heard Siracusans only drink tea when they're sick.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I couldn't have said it better.
But this is Lungmen, and we Lungmenites like our tea with more leaves, Mr. Cadeddu.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I have no opinion. I'm only here as a Messenger of the signora.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: But I hope you can understand that, no matter which land we walk, Siracusans are always Siracusans, and we Siracusans don't drink lukewarm tea.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Sure, but some of our friends from Siracusa have come to enjoy the aroma of our tea. Do you, or perhaps the signora you represent, really plan on forcing some other beverage into their mouths?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: The signora has no plans to interfere with them. Out of our respect for you, and as an apology for their transgression in Lungmen, you may deal with them as you see fit.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: I have to apologize to you, too. This morning, our locals mistook for an accomplice of theirs. That's why they brought you to their hideout.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Thank you for not killing any of them.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Please, no thanks necessary.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Well, then, if there is nothing else...
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Sorry, but there is.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Please, by all means.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: The signora has no intention of dealing with that undisciplined bunch in any way, but there are two men we must do something about.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: You mean those two 'lone wolves?'
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Exactly.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Showing the rest of them leniency is the most that the signora can tolerate, but she will not allow these two to cut ties with the pack.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: I have heard a few things about them. We won't interfere with the mutual grudge they hold with Siracusa.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: We appreciate your understanding.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Furthermore, you can rest assured that we will refrain from doing anything unnecessary during their stay in Lungmen. However, if they spend too much time outside fooling around, we will have to interfere.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: As long as you do so within the bounds of Lungmen's rules.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: We will try, but we can't promise anything.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Is that a threat?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Certainly not.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Then your choice of the word 'try' is quite worth chewing over.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I will get to the point. You don't want to break Lungmen's rules while you are in Lungmen.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: We don't want to, of course. To tell the truth, if we had the choice, we definitely wouldn't want any kind of conflict between us and Lungmen or its mighty Yanese protector.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: You think too highly of an old man like me.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: But some things must be done. I hope you can understand.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Then, for both our sakes, let us pray things won't progress to that point.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Pray? Can I take it that's where you stand?
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: With my greatest respect for Lady Sicilia, yes. That's where I ultimately stand.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Very well, I understand.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: To the best of our ability, we will try to keep things from progressing to that point.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Please excuse me now.
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Thank you for your hospitality. If the opportunity arises, perhaps we can invite you to Siracusa for a cup of quadruplo espresso?
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: I appreciate it.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: But, first thing's first, won't you finish that tea?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: A guest must wholeheartedly accept their host's hospitality. This, too, is one of Lungmen's rules.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: The black-clad Siracusan takes the teacup in front of him and finishes it in one go.
Will this do?
attributes.name: Cadeddu

attributes.content: Of course, my dear friend. Please travel safe.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Is he gone?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: He is. Our men followed him until he left the city. It didn't look like he was going to change disguises or anything.
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: You heard my conversation with the man just now, right?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: Get the word out. I want everyone to keep an eye out the Siracusan mafia.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I will.
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: As for the two lone wolves... We have Emperor keeping an eye on one of them. I'm not worried about her. But the other, keep a close eye on her until she leaves Lungmen.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: I will.
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: And what do we do if she doesn't leave?
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: Today is Friday, isn't it?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: That's right, but... What do you mean?
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: If memory serves, everyone always calls it... something Friday... What was it again? I can't say I know how you youngsters talk these days.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Anyway, Ice Castle Hotel has 30% off today, doesn't it?
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Uhh... I'll ask.
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: If they're running the discount, book a dinner for two for tonight.
attributes.name: Rat King

attributes.content: Dinner for two... Understood! On it!
attributes.name: Subordinate

attributes.content: Calm down. I'm just going to eat with an old friend.
attributes.name: Rat King
